#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:1
msgid "Package Configuration"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:3
msgid ""
"moon uses a package file to identify and describe a package. The legacy "
"format is `moon.pkg.json`, and the new format is `moon.pkg`. For full "
"JSON schema, please check [moon's "
"repository](https://github.com/moonbitlang/moon/blob/main/crates/moonbuild/template/pkg.schema.json)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:7
msgid "New format (`moon.pkg`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:9
msgid ""
"The new format is a concise DSL. You can generate or reformat it from an "
"existing `moon.pkg.json` with:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:12
msgid "moon fmt -C <module_dir>\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:16 ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:202
msgid "Example:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:18
msgid ""
"import {\n"
"  \"moonbit-community/language/packages/virtual\",\n"
"}\n"
"\n"
"options(\n"
"  \"is-main\": true,\n"
"  overrides: [ \"moonbit-community/language/packages/implement\" ],\n"
")\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:22
msgid ""
"In `moon.pkg`, dependencies are declared in an `import { ... }` block. "
"Use `@alias` to set a custom alias:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:25 ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:105
msgid ""
"import {\n"
"  \"moonbit-community/language/packages/pkgA\",\n"
"  \"moonbit-community/language/packages/pkgC\" @c,\n"
"  \"moonbitlang/core/builtin\",\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:29
msgid ""
"All other fields from `moon.pkg.json` move into a single `options(...)` "
"block. The key names and value shapes are unchanged; the legacy keys that"
" contain `-` must be quoted."
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:33
msgid ""
"options(\n"
"  \"virtual\": { \"has-default\": true },\n"
")\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:37
msgid "The `moon.pkg` format allows comments `//...`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:39
msgid "Full syntax of `moon.pkg` is as follows:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:41
msgid ""
"moon_pkg ::= statement*\n"
"statement ::= import | assign | apply\n"
"\n"
"import ::= \"import\" \"{\" (import_item \",\")* import_item? \"}\" "
"import_kind?\n"
"import_item ::= STRING (\"@\" PKG_NAME)?\n"
"import_kind ::= \"for\" STRING\n"
"\n"
"assign ::= LIDENT \"=\" expr\n"
"\n"
"apply ::= LIDENT \"(\" (argument \",\")* argument? \")\"\n"
"argument ::= LIDENT \":\" expr | STRING \":\" expr  \n"
"\n"
"expr ::= array | object | apply | STRING | INT | \"true\" | \"false\"\n"
"array ::= \"[\" (expr \",\")* expr? \"]\"\n"
"object ::= \"{\" (field \",\")* field? \"}\"\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:59
msgid "Name"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:61
msgid ""
"The package name is not configurable; it is determined by the directory "
"name of the package."
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:63
msgid "is-main"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:65
msgid ""
"The `is-main` field is used to specify whether a package needs to be "
"linked into an executable file."
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:67
msgid ""
"The output of the linking process depends on the backend. When this field"
" is set to `true`:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:69
msgid ""
"For the Wasm and `wasm-gc` backends, a standalone WebAssembly module will"
" be generated."
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:70
msgid "For the `js` backend, a standalone JavaScript file will be generated."
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md
msgid "moon.pkg"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:76
msgid ""
"options(\n"
"  \"is-main\": true,\n"
")\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md
msgid "moon.pkg.json"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:85
msgid ""
"{\n"
"  \"is-main\": true\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:93
msgid "Importing dependencies"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:95
msgid "Import"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:97
msgid ""
"The `import` field is used to specify other packages that a package "
"depends on."
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:99
msgid ""
"For example, the following imports `pkgA` and `pkgC`, aliasing `pkgC` to "
"`c`. User can write `@c` to access definitions from `pkgC`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:111
msgid ""
"{\n"
"    \"import\": [\n"
"        \"moonbit-community/language/packages/pkgA\",\n"
"        {\n"
"            \"path\": \"moonbit-community/language/packages/pkgC\",\n"
"            \"alias\": \"c\"\n"
"        },\n"
"        \"moonbitlang/core/builtin\"\n"
"    ]\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:118
msgid ""
"Most core packages are not special here: if you use `@json`, `@test`, or "
"other ordinary core aliases, add the corresponding `moonbitlang/core/...`"
" package to `import` to avoid `core_package_not_imported` warnings."
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:122
msgid ""
"`prelude` is the exception. It is available by default, so the names it "
"exposes do not need an explicit package import."
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:125
msgid "Test import"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:127
msgid ""
"The test import is used to specify other packages that the black-box test"
" package of this package depends on, with the same format as `import`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:132
msgid ""
"import {\n"
"  \"path/to/package1\",\n"
"  \"path/to/package2\" @pkg2,\n"
"} for \"test\"\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:140
msgid ""
"{\n"
"  \"test-import\": {\n"
"    \"path/to/package1\",\n"
"    {\n"
"      \"path\": \"path/to/package2\",\n"
"      \"alias\": \"pkg2\"\n"
"    }\n"
"  }\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:154
msgid ""
"The `test-import-all` field is used to specify whether all public "
"definitions from the package being tested should be imported (`true`) by "
"default."
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:156
msgid "White-box test import"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:158
msgid ""
"The white-box test import is used to specify other packages that the "
"white-box test package of this package depends on, with the same format "
"as `import`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:163
msgid ""
"import {\n"
"  \"path/to/package1\",\n"
"  \"path/to/package2\" @pkg2,\n"
"} for \"wbtest\"\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:171
msgid ""
"{\n"
"  \"wbtest-import\": {\n"
"    \"path/to/package1\",\n"
"    {\n"
"      \"path\": \"path/to/package2\",\n"
"      \"alias\": \"pkg2\"\n"
"    }\n"
"  }\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:185
msgid "Conditional Compilation"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:187
msgid "The smallest unit of conditional compilation is a file."
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:189
msgid ""
"In a conditional compilation expression, three logical operators are "
"supported: `and`, `or`, and `not`, where the `or` operator can be "
"omitted."
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:191
msgid ""
"For example, `[\"or\", \"wasm\", \"wasm-gc\"]` can be simplified to "
"`[\"wasm\", \"wasm-gc\"]`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:193
msgid ""
"Conditions in the expression can be categorized into backends and "
"optimization levels:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:195
msgid "**Backend conditions**: `\"wasm\"`, `\"wasm-gc\"`, and `\"js\"`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:196
msgid "**Optimization level conditions**: `\"debug\"` and `\"release\"`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:198
msgid "Conditional expressions support nesting."
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:200
msgid ""
"If a file is not listed in `\"targets\"`, it will be compiled under all "
"conditions by default."
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:206
msgid ""
"options(\n"
"  targets: {\n"
"    \"only_js.mbt\": [\"js\"],\n"
"    \"only_wasm.mbt\": [\"wasm\"],\n"
"    \"only_wasm_gc.mbt\": [\"wasm-gc\"],\n"
"    \"all_wasm.mbt\": [\"wasm\", \"wasm-gc\"],\n"
"    \"not_js.mbt\": [\"not\", \"js\"],\n"
"    \"only_debug.mbt\": [\"debug\"],\n"
"    \"js_and_release.mbt\": [\"and\", [\"js\"], [\"release\"]],\n"
"    \"js_only_test.mbt\": [\"js\"],\n"
"    \"js_or_wasm.mbt\": [\"js\", \"wasm\"],\n"
"    \"wasm_release_or_js_debug.mbt\": [\"or\", [\"and\", \"wasm\", "
"\"release\"], [\"and\", \"js\", \"debug\"]]\n"
"  }\n"
")\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:225
msgid ""
"{\n"
"  \"targets\": {\n"
"    \"only_js.mbt\": [\"js\"],\n"
"    \"only_wasm.mbt\": [\"wasm\"],\n"
"    \"only_wasm_gc.mbt\": [\"wasm-gc\"],\n"
"    \"all_wasm.mbt\": [\"wasm\", \"wasm-gc\"],\n"
"    \"not_js.mbt\": [\"not\", \"js\"],\n"
"    \"only_debug.mbt\": [\"debug\"],\n"
"    \"js_and_release.mbt\": [\"and\", [\"js\"], [\"release\"]],\n"
"    \"js_only_test.mbt\": [\"js\"],\n"
"    \"js_or_wasm.mbt\": [\"js\", \"wasm\"],\n"
"    \"wasm_release_or_js_debug.mbt\": [\"or\", [\"and\", \"wasm\", "
"\"release\"], [\"and\", \"js\", \"debug\"]]\n"
"  }\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:244
msgid "Supported Targets"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:246
msgid ""
"The `supported-targets` option declares which backends a package is "
"intended to support. It uses a target-set expression, not an array:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:251
msgid ""
"options(\n"
"  \"supported-targets\": \"js\",\n"
")\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:258
msgid ""
"{\n"
"  \"supported-targets\": \"js\"\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:266
msgid "Examples:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:268
msgid "`js` for a single backend"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:269
msgid "`+js+wasm-gc` for an explicit set of backends"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:270
msgid "`+all-js` for all backends except `js`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:272
msgid "Legacy array syntax is still accepted for compatibility:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:274
msgid ""
"{\n"
"  \"supported-targets\": [\"js\", \"native\"]\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:280
msgid "This is package metadata, not a conditional compilation rule:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:282
msgid "use `supported-targets` to declare the package's supported backend set"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:283
msgid ""
"use `targets` to include or exclude individual files for different "
"backends"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:284
msgid ""
"use `preferred-target` in `moon.mod.json` to choose the default backend "
"for commands such as `moon check`, `moon run`, and `moon build`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:286
msgid ""
"When both the module and the package declare `supported-targets`, the "
"effective backend set is their intersection."
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:289
msgid "Command behavior follows the selected backend:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:291
msgid ""
"`moon check`, `moon build`, `moon test`, and `moon bench` keep only "
"packages that support the selected backend"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:292
msgid "`moon run` requires the selected package to support the selected backend"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:293
msgid "`moon info` skips unsupported selected packages with a warning"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:294
msgid ""
"`moon bundle` skips package targets that do not support the selected "
"backend"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:296
msgid ""
"After root selection, Moon also checks reachable required dependencies. "
"If a required dependency does not support the selected backend, the "
"command fails with a normal user-facing error."
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:299
msgid "Notes:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:301
msgid "omitting `supported-targets` means all backends are supported"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:302
msgid ""
"`--target all` expands to `wasm`, `wasm-gc`, `js`, and `native`, but not "
"`llvm`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:303
msgid "`llvm` is still a valid `supported-targets` value"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:304
msgid "legacy array syntax is deprecated, but still accepted for compatibility"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:306
msgid "A common setup is:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:308
msgid "mark a native-only package with `\"supported-targets\": \"native\"`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:309
msgid "set `\"preferred-target\": \"native\"` in `moon.mod.json`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:310
msgid "use `targets` only when some files inside the package differ by backend"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:312
msgid "Link Options"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:314
msgid ""
"By default, moon only links packages where `is-main` is set to `true`. If"
" you need to link other packages, you can specify this with the `link` "
"option."
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:316
msgid ""
"The `link` option is used to specify link options, and its value can be "
"either a boolean or an object."
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:318
msgid ""
"When the `link` value is `true`, it indicates that the package should be "
"linked. The output will vary depending on the backend specified during "
"the build."
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:322
msgid ""
"options(\n"
"  link: true\n"
")\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:329
msgid ""
"{\n"
"  \"link\": true\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:337
msgid ""
"When the `link` value is an object, it indicates that the package should "
"be linked, and you can specify link options. For detailed configuration, "
"please refer to the subpage for the corresponding backend."
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:339
msgid "Wasm Backend Link Options"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:341
msgid "Common Options"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:343
msgid ""
"The `exports` option is used to specify the function names exported by "
"the Wasm backend."
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:345
msgid ""
"For example, in the following configuration, the `hello` function from "
"the current package is exported as the `hello` function in the Wasm "
"module, and the `foo` function is exported as the `bar` function in the "
"Wasm module. In the Wasm host, the `hello` and `bar` functions can be "
"called to invoke the `hello` and `foo` functions from the current "
"package."
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:349
msgid ""
"options(\n"
"  link: {\n"
"    \"wasm\": {\n"
"      \"exports\": [ \"hello\", \"foo:bar\" ],\n"
"    },\n"
"    \"wasm-gc\": {\n"
"      \"exports\": [ \"hello\", \"foo:bar\" ],\n"
"    }\n"
"  }\n"
")\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:363
msgid ""
"{\n"
"  \"link\": {\n"
"    \"wasm\": {\n"
"      \"exports\": [\n"
"        \"hello\",\n"
"        \"foo:bar\"\n"
"      ]\n"
"    },\n"
"    \"wasm-gc\": {\n"
"      \"exports\": [\n"
"        \"hello\",\n"
"        \"foo:bar\"\n"
"      ]\n"
"    }\n"
"  }\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:384
msgid ""
"The `import-memory` option is used to specify the linear memory imported "
"by the Wasm module."
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:386
msgid ""
"For example, the following configuration specifies that the linear memory"
" imported by the Wasm module is the `memory` variable from the `env` "
"module."
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:390
msgid ""
"options(\n"
"  link: {\n"
"    \"wasm\": {\n"
"      \"import-memory\": {\n"
"        \"module\": \"env\",\n"
"        \"name\": \"memory\",\n"
"      },\n"
"    },\n"
"    \"wasm-gc\": {\n"
"      \"import-memory\": {\n"
"        \"module\": \"env\",\n"
"        \"name\": \"memory\",\n"
"      },\n"
"    },\n"
"  },\n"
")\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:410
msgid ""
"{\n"
"  \"link\": {\n"
"    \"wasm\": {\n"
"      \"import-memory\": {\n"
"        \"module\": \"env\",\n"
"        \"name\": \"memory\"\n"
"      }\n"
"    },\n"
"    \"wasm-gc\": {\n"
"      \"import-memory\": {\n"
"        \"module\": \"env\",\n"
"        \"name\": \"memory\"\n"
"      }\n"
"    }\n"
"  }\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:431
msgid ""
"The `export-memory-name` option is used to specify the name of the linear"
" memory exported by the Wasm module."
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:435
msgid ""
"options(\n"
"  link: {\n"
"    \"wasm\": {\n"
"      \"export-memory-name\": \"memory\",\n"
"    },\n"
"    \"wasm-gc\": {\n"
"      \"export-memory-name\": \"memory\",\n"
"    },\n"
"  },\n"
")\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:449
msgid ""
"{\n"
"  \"link\": {\n"
"    \"wasm\": {\n"
"      \"export-memory-name\": \"memory\"\n"
"    },\n"
"    \"wasm-gc\": {\n"
"      \"export-memory-name\": \"memory\"\n"
"    }\n"
"  }\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:464
msgid "Wasm Linear Backend Link Options"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:466
msgid ""
"The `heap-start-address` option is used to specify the starting address "
"of the linear memory that can be used when compiling to the Wasm backend."
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:468
msgid ""
"For example, the following configuration sets the starting address of the"
" linear memory to 1024."
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:472
msgid ""
"options(\n"
"  link: {\n"
"    \"wasm\": {\n"
"      \"heap-start-address\": 1024,\n"
"    },\n"
"  },\n"
")\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:483
msgid ""
"{\n"
"  \"link\": {\n"
"    \"wasm\": {\n"
"      \"heap-start-address\": 1024\n"
"    }\n"
"  }\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:495
msgid "Wasm GC Backend Link Options"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:497
msgid ""
"The `use-js-string-builtin` option is used to specify whether the [JS "
"String Builtin Proposal](https://github.com/WebAssembly/js-string-"
"builtins/blob/main/proposals/js-string-builtins/Overview.md) should be "
"enabled when compiling to the Wasm GC backend.  It will make the `String`"
" in MoonBit equivalent to the `String` in JavaScript host runtime."
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:500
msgid "For example, the following configuration enables the JS String Builtin."
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:504
msgid ""
"options(\n"
"  link: {\n"
"    \"wasm-gc\": {\n"
"      \"use-js-builtin-string\": true,\n"
"    },\n"
"  },\n"
")\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:515
msgid ""
"{\n"
"  \"link\": {\n"
"    \"wasm-gc\": {\n"
"      \"use-js-builtin-string\": true\n"
"    }\n"
"  }\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:527
msgid ""
"The `imported-string-constants` option is used to specify the imported "
"string namespace used by the JS String Builtin Proposal, which is \"_\" "
"by default. It should meet the configuration in the JS host runtime."
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:530
msgid ""
"For example, the following configuration and JS initialization configures"
" the imported string namespace."
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:534
msgid ""
"options(\n"
"  link: {\n"
"    \"wasm-gc\": {\n"
"      \"use-js-builtin-string\": true,\n"
"      \"imported-string-constants\": \"_\",\n"
"    },\n"
"  },\n"
")\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:546
msgid ""
"{\n"
"  \"link\": {\n"
"    \"wasm-gc\": {\n"
"      \"use-js-builtin-string\": true,\n"
"      \"imported-string-constants\": \"_\"\n"
"    }\n"
"  }\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:559
msgid ""
"const { instance } = await WebAssembly.instantiate(bytes, {}, { "
"importedStringConstants: \"strings\" });\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:563
msgid "JS Backend Link Options"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:565
msgid ""
"The `exports` option is used to specify the function names to export in "
"the JavaScript module."
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:567
msgid ""
"For example, in the following configuration, the `hello` function from "
"the current package is exported as the `hello` function in the JavaScript"
" module. In the JavaScript host, the `hello` function can be called to "
"invoke the `hello` function from the current package."
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:571
msgid ""
"options(\n"
"  link: {\n"
"    \"js\": {\n"
"      \"exports\": [ \"hello\" ],\n"
"    },\n"
"  },\n"
")\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:582
msgid ""
"{\n"
"  \"link\": {\n"
"    \"js\": {\n"
"      \"exports\": [\n"
"        \"hello\"\n"
"      ]\n"
"    }\n"
"  }\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:596
msgid ""
"The `format` option is used to specify the output format of the "
"JavaScript module."
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:598
msgid "The currently supported formats are:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:599
msgid "`esm` (default)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:600
msgid "`cjs`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:601
msgid "`iife`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:603
msgid ""
"For example, the following configuration sets the output format of the "
"current package to ES Module."
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:607
msgid ""
"options(\n"
"  link: {\n"
"    \"js\": {\n"
"      \"format\": \"esm\",\n"
"    },\n"
"  },\n"
")\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:618
msgid ""
"{\n"
"  \"link\": {\n"
"    \"js\": {\n"
"      \"format\": \"esm\"\n"
"    }\n"
"  }\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:630
msgid "Native Backend Link Options"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:632
msgid ""
"The `cc` option is used to specify the compiler for compiling the "
"`moonc`-generated C source files. It can be either a full path to the "
"compiler or a simple name that is accessible via the PATH environment "
"variable."
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:637
msgid ""
"options(\n"
"  link: {\n"
"    \"native\": {\n"
"      \"cc\": \"/usr/bin/gcc13\",\n"
"    },\n"
"  },\n"
")\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:648
msgid ""
"{\n"
"  \"link\": {\n"
"    \"native\": {\n"
"      \"cc\": \"/usr/bin/gcc13\"\n"
"    }\n"
"  }\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:660
msgid ""
"The `cc-flags` option is used to override the default flags passed to the"
" compiler. For example, you can use the following flag to define a macro "
"called MOONBIT."
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:665
msgid ""
"options(\n"
"  link: {\n"
"    \"native\": {\n"
"      \"cc-flags\": \"-DMOONBIT\",\n"
"    },\n"
"  },\n"
")\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:676
msgid ""
"{\n"
"  \"link\": {\n"
"    \"native\": {\n"
"      \"cc-flags\": \"-DMOONBIT\"\n"
"    }\n"
"  }\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:688
msgid ""
"The `cc-link-flags` option is used to override the default flags passed "
"to the linker. Since the linker is invoked through the compiler driver "
"(e.g., `cc` instead of `ld`, `cl` instead of `link`), you should prefix "
"specific options with `-Wl,` or `/link ` when passing them."
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:692
msgid "The following example strips symbol information from produced binary."
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:696
msgid ""
"options(\n"
"  link: {\n"
"    \"native\": {\n"
"      \"cc-link-flags\": \"-s\",\n"
"    },\n"
"  },\n"
")\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:707
msgid ""
"{\n"
"  \"link\": {\n"
"    \"native\": {\n"
"      \"cc-link-flags\": \"-s\"\n"
"    }\n"
"  }\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:719
msgid ""
"The `stub-cc` option is similar to `cc` but controls which compiler to "
"use for compiling stubs. Although it can be different from `cc`, it is "
"not recommended and should only be used for debugging purposes. "
"Therefore, we strongly recommend to specify `cc` and `stub-cc` at the "
"same time and make them consistent to avoid potential conflicts."
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:724
msgid ""
"The `stub-cc-flags` is similar to `cc-flags`. It only have effects on "
"stubs compilation."
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:726
msgid ""
"The `stub-cc-link-flags` are similar but have a subtle difference.  "
"Normally, stubs are compiled into object files and linked against object "
"files generated from `moonc`-generated C source files.  This linking is "
"only controlled by `cc-flags` and `cc-link-flags`, as mentioned earlier."
"  However, in specific modes, such as when the fast-debugging-test "
"feature is enabled, there will be a separate linking procedure for stub "
"objects files, where  `stub-cc-link-flags` will take effect."
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:733
msgid "Default C compiler and compiler flags for the native backend"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:735
msgid ""
"Here is a brief summarization to "
"[compiler_flags.rs](https://github.com/moonbitlang/moon/blob/main/crates/moonutil/src/compiler_flags.rs)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:737
msgid "C Compiler"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:739
msgid "Search in PATH for the following items from top to bottom."
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:741
msgid "cl"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:742
msgid "gcc"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:743
msgid "clang"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:744
msgid "cc"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:745
msgid "the internal tcc"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:747
msgid ""
"For GCC-like compilers, the default compile & link command is as follows."
" `[]` is used to indicate the flags may not exist in some modes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:749
msgid ""
"cc -o $target -I$MOON_HOME/include -L$MOON_HOME/lib [-g] [-shared -fPIC] "
"\\\n"
"   -fwrapv -fno-strict-aliasing (-O2|-Og) "
"[$MOON_HOME/lib/libmoonbitrun.o] \\\n"
"   $sources -lm $cc_flags $cc_link_flags\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:755
msgid "For MSVC, the default compile & link command is as follows."
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:756
msgid ""
"cl (/Fo|/Fe)$target -I$MOON_HOME/include [/LD] /utf-8 /wd4819 /nologo "
"(/O2|/Od) \\\n"
"   /link /LIBPATH:$MOON_HOME/lib\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:761
msgid "Pre-build"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:763
msgid ""
"The `\"pre-build\"` field is used to specify pre-build commands, which "
"will be executed before build commands such as `moon check|build|test`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:765
msgid ""
"`\"pre-build\"` is an array, where each element is an object containing "
"`input`, `output`, and `command` fields. The `input` and `output` fields "
"can be strings or arrays of strings, while the `command` field is a "
"string. In the `command`, you can use any shell commands, as well as the "
"`$input` and `$output` variables, which represent the input and output "
"files, respectively. If these fields are arrays, they will be joined with"
" spaces by default."
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:767
msgid ""
"Currently, there is a built-in special command `:embed`, which converts "
"files into MoonBit source code. The `--text` parameter is used to embed "
"text files, and `--binary` is used for binary files. `--text` is the "
"default and can be omitted. The `--name` parameter is used to specify the"
" generated variable name, with `resource` being the default. The command "
"is executed in the directory where the `moon.pkg.json` file is located."
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:771
msgid ""
"options(\n"
"  \"pre-build\": [\n"
"    {\n"
"      \"input\": \"a.txt\",\n"
"      \"output\": \"a.mbt\",\n"
"      \"command\": \":embed -i $input -o $output\",\n"
"    },\n"
"  ],\n"
")\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:784
msgid ""
"{\n"
"  \"pre-build\": [\n"
"    {\n"
"      \"input\": \"a.txt\",\n"
"      \"output\": \"a.mbt\",\n"
"      \"command\": \":embed -i $input -o $output\"\n"
"    }\n"
"  ]\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:798
msgid "If the content of `a.txt` in the current package directory is:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:799
msgid ""
"hello,\n"
"world\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:804
msgid ""
"After running `moon build`, the following `a.mbt` file will be generated "
"in the directory where the `moon.pkg.json` is located:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:806
msgid ""
"let resource : String =\n"
"  #|hello,\n"
"  #|world\n"
"  #|\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:813
msgid "Warnings List"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:815
msgid ""
"Used to disable warnings, enable warnings, or treat a warning as a fatal "
"error. The warning list is a string composed of multiple warning name, "
"each prefixed with a sign:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:818
msgid "`-` to disable the warning"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:819
msgid "`+` to enable the warning"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:820
msgid "`@` to treat the enabled warning as a fatal error"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:822
msgid ""
"For example, in the following configuration, `-unused_value` disables the"
" unused functions and variables warning."
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:826
msgid "warnings = \"-unused_value\"\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:831
msgid ""
"{\n"
"  \"warn-list\": \"-unused_value\"\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:839
msgid ""
"If multiple warnings need to be disabled, they can be directly connected "
"and combined."
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:843
msgid "warnings = \"-unused_value-unreachable_code\"\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:848
msgid ""
"{\n"
"  \"warn-list\": \"-unused_value-unreachable_code\"\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:856
msgid ""
"If it is necessary to activate certain warnings that were originally "
"prohibited, use the plus sign."
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:860
msgid "warnings = \"+unused_optional_argument\"\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:865
msgid ""
"{\n"
"  \"warn-list\": \"+unused_optional_argument\"\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:873
msgid "To treat a warning as a fatal error, use the `@`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:877
msgid "warnings = \"@deprecated\"\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:882
msgid ""
"{\n"
"  \"warn-list\": \"@deprecated\"\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:890
msgid ""
"You can also use warnings number in warning list. Here is the full list "
"of warning names:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:892
msgid ""
"Available warnings:\n"
"    name                           description\n"
"  1 unused_value                   Unused variable or function.\n"
"  2 unused_value                   Unused variable.\n"
"  3 unused_type_declaration        Unused type declaration.\n"
"  4 missing_priv                   Unused abstract type.\n"
"  5 unused_type_variable           Unused type variable.\n"
"  6 unused_constructor             Unused constructor.\n"
"  7 unused_field                   Unused field or constructor argument.\n"
"  8 redundant_modifier             Redundant modifier.\n"
"  9 struct_never_constructed       Struct never constructed.\n"
" 10 unused_pattern                 Unused pattern.\n"
" 11 partial_match                  Partial pattern matching.\n"
" 12 unreachable_code               Unreachable code.\n"
" 13 unresolved_type_variable       Unresolved type variable.\n"
" 14 alert or alert_<category>      All alerts or alerts with specific "
"category.\n"
" 15 unused_mut                     Unused mutability.\n"
" 16 parser_inconsistency           Parser inconsistency check.\n"
" 17 ambiguous_loop_argument        Ambiguous usage of loop argument.\n"
" 18 useless_loop                   Useless loop expression.\n"
" 19 toplevel_not_left_aligned      Top_level declaration is not left "
"aligned.\n"
" 20 deprecated                     Deprecated API usage.\n"
" 21 missing_pattern_arguments      Some arguments of constructor are "
"omitted in pattern.\n"
" 22 ambiguous_block                Ambiguous block.\n"
" 23 unused_try                     Useless try expression.\n"
" 24 unused_error_type              Useless error type.\n"
" 25 test_unqualified_package       Using implicitly imported API in test."
"\n"
" 26 unused_catch_all               Useless catch all.\n"
" 27 deprecated_syntax              Deprecated syntax.\n"
" 28 todo                           Todo\n"
" 29 unused_package                 Unused package.\n"
" 30 missing_package_alias          Empty package alias.\n"
" 31 unused_optional_argument       Optional argument never supplied.\n"
" 32 unused_default_value           Default value of optional argument "
"never used.\n"
" 33 text_segment_excceed           Text segment exceed the line or column"
" limits.\n"
" 34 implicit_use_builtin           Implicit use of definitions from "
"`moonbitlang/core/builtin`.\n"
" 35 reserved_keyword               Reserved keyword.\n"
" 36 loop_label_shadowing           Loop label shadows another label.\n"
" 37 unused_loop_label              Unused loop label.\n"
" 38 missing_invariant              For-loop is missing an invariant.\n"
" 39 missing_reasoning              For-loop is missing a reasoning.\n"
" 41 missing_rest_mark              Missing `..` in map pattern.\n"
" 42 invalid_attribute              Invalid attribute.\n"
" 43 unused_attribute               Unused attribute.\n"
" 44 invalid_inline_wasm            Invalid inline-wasm.\n"
" 46 unused_rest_mark               Useless `..` in pattern\n"
" 47 invalid_mbti                   Invalid mbti file\n"
" 48 missing_default_impl_mark      Trait method with default "
"implementation not marked with `= _`\n"
" 49 missing_definition             Unused pub definition because it does "
"not exist in mbti file.\n"
" 50 method_shadowing               Local method shadows upstream method\n"
" 51 ambiguous_precedence           Ambiguous operator precedence\n"
" 52 unused_loop_variable           Loop variable not updated in loop\n"
" 53 unused_trait_bound             Unused trait bound\n"
" 55 unannotated_ffi                Unannotated FFI param type\n"
" 56 missing_pattern_field          Missing field in struct pattern\n"
" 57 missing_pattern_payload        Constructor pattern expect payload\n"
" 58 unused_non_capturing           Unnecessary non-capturing group in "
"regex\n"
" 59 unaligned_byte_access          Unaligned byte access in bits pattern\n"
" 60 unused_struct_update           Unused struct update\n"
" 61 duplicate_test                 Duplicate test name\n"
" 62 invalid_cascade                Calling method with non-unit return "
"type via `..`\n"
" 63 syntax_lint                    Syntax lint warning\n"
" 64 unannotated_toplevel_array     Unannotated toplevel array\n"
" 65 prefer_readonly_array          Suggest ReadOnlyArray for read-only "
"array literal\n"
" 66 prefer_fixed_array             Suggest FixedArray for mutated array "
"literal\n"
" 67 unused_async                   Useless `async` annotation\n"
" 68 declaration_unimplemented      Declaration is unimplemented\n"
" 69 declaration_implemented        Declaration is already implemented\n"
" 70 deprecated_for_in_method       using `iterator()` method for `for .. "
"in` loop.\n"
"  A                                all warnings\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:966
msgid ""
"Use `moonc build-package -warn-help` to see the list of preset compiler "
"warnings."
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:969
msgid "Alert Warning"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:971
msgid ""
"Alerts are special warnings that indicate the usage of API marked with  "
"[`#internal` attribute](../../language/attributes.md#internal-attribute)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:974
msgid ""
"All alerts has a category associated with it, which is customized by the "
"author of the API. You can enable or disable specific alert categories "
"using the `alert_<category>` warning name, or use `alert` to control all "
"alert warnings at once."
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:978
msgid ""
"For example, in the following configuration, all warnings for alerts are "
"treated  as fatal errors, except for the `unsafe` category, which is "
"disabled."
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:983
msgid "warnings = \"@alert-alert_unsafe\" \n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:988
msgid ""
"{\n"
"  \"warn-list\": \"@alert-alert_unsafe\" \n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:996
msgid "Virtual Package"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:998
msgid ""
"A virtual package serves as an interface of a package that can be "
"replaced by actual implementations."
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:1000
msgid "Declarations"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:1002
msgid ""
"The `virtual` field is used to declare the current package as a virtual "
"package."
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:1004
msgid ""
"For example, the following declares a virtual package with default "
"implementation:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:1008
msgid ""
"options(\n"
"  virtual: {\n"
"    \"has-default\": true,\n"
"  },\n"
")\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:1017
msgid ""
"{\n"
"  \"virtual\": {\n"
"    \"has-default\": true\n"
"  }\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:1027
msgid "Implementations"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:1029
msgid ""
"The `implement` field is used to declare the virtual package to be "
"implemented by the current package."
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:1031
msgid "For example, the following implements a virtual package:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:1035
msgid ""
"options(\n"
"  implement: \"moonbitlang/core/abort\",\n"
")\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:1042
msgid ""
"{\n"
"  \"implement\": \"moonbitlang/core/abort\"\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:1050
msgid "Overriding implementations"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:1052
msgid ""
"The `overrides` field is used to provide the implementations that "
"fulfills an imported virtual package."
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:1054
msgid ""
"For example, the following overrides the default implementation of the "
"builtin abort package with another package:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:1058
msgid ""
"options(\n"
"  overrides: [ \"moonbitlang/dummy_abort/abort_show_msg\" ],\n"
")\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:1065
msgid ""
"{\n"
"  \"overrides\": [\"moonbitlang/dummy_abort/abort_show_msg\"]\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

